---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="AI-assisted Security Review">
  <h1>AI-assisted security review</h1>
  <p>
    Separate from code review on a pull request, this is the automated layer that watches the
    <em>supply chain</em> continuously:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dependabot alerts</strong> — flags the outdated Markdown renderer this site's feedback widget depends on, and opens the upgrade PR</li>
    <li><strong>Dependency review</strong> — blocks a pull request from introducing a new vulnerable dependency</li>
    <li><strong>Secret scanning with push protection</strong> — catches a credential before it's committed, and flags one that already was</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Where Copilot Code Review looks at a diff, this layer looks at the whole dependency graph and
    commit history — the exact surface OWASP's A03: Software Supply Chain Failures is about.
  </p>
</Layout>
